Fossils of a creature bearing a 'striking' similarity to depictions of Nessie have been found in Inverness Museum and Art Gallery .
The fossils were rediscovered when the president of the Official Loch Ness Fan Club, Gary Campbell, was invited to the museum and spotted them .
'Pterichththyodes milleri - or 'wing-fish' - roamed Earth's lakes during the Paleozoic Era, between 542 million and 251 million years ago .